p: Next, we performed GO and KEGG pathway enrichment analyses. The results showed that at the biological process level, the GO functions of differentially expressed mRNAs mainly mediated processes including gland development, DNA replication, and urogenital system development ( Figure 2A); at the cell component level, differentially expressed mRNAs were mainly involved in the mitochondrial inner membrane ( Figure 2B); and at the molecular function level, differentially expressed mRNAs were mainly enriched in ATPase activity and catalytic activity acting on DNA ( Figure 2C).
